Endosteum lines the:
marrow cavity
trabeculae of spongy bone
central & perforating canals of compact bone
It is an incomplete layer consisting of osteoprogenitor cells, osteoblasts, bone-lining cells and osteoclasts.
It functions in bone growth, repair, remodeling.
